1111111111.content:
Choose Your Tale...

Harry Potter WG Interactive 01
So, Harry Potter interests you? Good, me too. But this is going to be a bit of an alternate universe, where Voldemort's defeat happened a lot quicker and a lot better for all concerned. Basically, everybody came out of it alive and well.

The Plot
After Tom Riddle's death, Ginny and Hermione are meeting the whole Weasley clan at the Burrow to celebrate Bill and Fleur's wedding.

There, we see that *every* Weasley man (any man who is born to the family, and any man who is brought into the family by adoption, marriage, or simply friendship) is a feeder and a fat admirer.

At the same time, we find out that *every* Weasley women (any woman who is born to the family, and any woman who is brought into the family by adoption, marriage, or simply friendship) is a feedee and a gainer with magic helping them to get even fatter, even faster.

Not only that, but Fleur is part Veela, making her liable to literally change appearance to suit her lover. When Veela marry feeders, they get very fat quite quickly, even when they don't marry a Weasley. And, of course, Ginny has always been a Weasley woman, now a young adult. Even Hermione is becoming a Weasley woman, dating into the family...

But Kaylee will be quite chubby already.

11111111111.content:
Hermione loosened the buttons on her dress, letting her stomach ease out a little. At any other wedding, she might have felt a little embarrassed at how many slices of cake she'd eaten, but here she felt positively anorexic by comparison. The Weasley's knew how to throw a wedding, it seemed, and every table got it's own layer of the enormous cake. All of it had been eaten, even at the Bride and Groom's head table, with only Bill and Fleur.

Fleur had sat down after the first dance to cut the cake and hadn't stood up again since. A sort of decoration on the front of her wedding dress had been unstrapped and pulled away, to reveal her stomach. Bill and Fleur had spent the rest of the night recieving well-wishes from guests at their own table, while Bill gradually fed Fleur the entire slab of wedding cake from their table. By the time Hermione had thought to loosen her own dress, Fleur already looked pregnant.

Hermione knew all about the Weasley women's weight gain, ever since she'd seen Ginny begin to out-pace Ron in the school feasts at Hogwarts and asked her what was wrong. It was all down to a strong urge to gorge yourself that arose in any Weasley woman a few years after puberty, or in any woman at all, when they started getting serious about being a Weasley, either through a late adoption or from a marriage. As she'd thought about it, Hermione had realised that Ron was probably the reason she'd had to loosen her bridesmaid's dress.

Leaning back in her chair, Hermione absently patted a softening paunch, and looked at the Weasley family at Fleur's wedding. Fleur, Ginny, and Hermione were each staying at the Burrow, but the rest were camping in the gardens and the fields around them. There just wasn't room in the Burrow for any more people. And, looking out at the crowd, Hermione could see a lot of faces that Molly said were almost unfamiliar.

When the expanded Weasley family realised that Voldemort was truly dead, that his followers were expelled from power, a lot of them flocked back to Britain from foreign shores. Weasleys who had married muggles or muggleborns returned. Weasleys who were the children of a Weasley and a muggle visited their parents homeland now that it wasn't a haven for pure-blood supremacists and dark lords.

Many of them had found new romance in Britain, from people eager to date these exotic relatives of the family that had brought down the dark lord. All this field, full of family and their new partners. It was just what Harry had always wanted. Looking round at him, she realised that there was still a chunk of wedding cake left on their table. Without really thinking about it, she dutifully sliced off another thick piece, hardly noticing what she was doing.

Cream, chewy icing, and the light, moist sponge filled her mouth again, as she chewed. Hermione's loosened dress gaped ever more at the carefully placed expanding belly section, as she continued subconciously eating the way that she had since the food was first brought out. This fifth slice of cake went down less easily than the first, but still she ate. She ate as she watched the people around her eating, almost without realising that she was a part of it.

It was only when the cake was all finished across the room that she realised just how much she'd had. Her fair share of that meal had been more food than she ever eaten in a single sitting before. The cake alone, even split with Ginny and an American Weasley cousin, had probably been more food than Hermione had ever eaten all at once. Yet she didn't feel bloated, didn't feel sluggish or painful. She just felt her belly weigh down on her lap.

Ginny looked similarly at peace. Her belly full of cake was a taut, round weight between her legs and on top of her lap. Her hands rested together on top of the dome that her belly had become, separating out her full breasts. The part of the bridesmaid's dress that Hermione could no longer see on herself was stretched out smooth on Ginny, pulled by the mass of the belly she was building behind it. Hermione supposed that it looked the same on hers.

Fleur, of course, was rather more extreme. It was clear why she had needed a wedding dress with a removable panel, rather than just an expanding waist. Her swollen stomach had bulged out with food, well past the point of her knees. Fleur looked like she was about ready to give birth to eight babies, except that she showed no signs of discomfort. She had no stretchmarks, no trouble breathing, nothing but a huge, perfectly round, pot-belly full of wedding cake.

Now that Ginny, Hermione, and Fleur have all been hit by the Weasley family weight gain, are they just going to eat, oblivious to the effect it is having on their body, like Molly did when she started seriously dating Arthur?

Or, are these three *really* going to go for a fattening? A bunch of women really *trying* to gain weight, as much as they can, as fast as they can?

(For those of you who like the numbers, Fleur now weighs 85kg, at the wedding. Ginny now weighs 65kg, at the wedding. Hermione now weighs 60kg, at the wedding.)

After the wedding, with no more Dark Lords in Britain, most of the enormous extended Weasley clan stuck around. Britain in general, and magical Britain in particular, was filled with feeder wizards and feedee witches. Even muggles started to see a sudden rise in the number of fat women and fat loving men and women. Heck, more than a few of them had friends or family meet a new boyfriend or girlfriend and suddenly gorging till they get incredibly fat, almost impossibly fast. But nobody seems to find it strange. Least of all, Fleur, Ginny, and Hermione, who simply gorge two or three times as much as they would have done, if there were not so many others around who made it seem somehow less strange. We check in after another month of this, even taking in the sight of a few fat, gorging muggles on the way.

Harry realised that Ginny was actually eating more than himself and Ron put together. At the end of the first day, as she kissed him goodnight, she hugged him, and he felt her swollen stomach pressing up against his erection.

In fact, it wasn't until the second day, when Harry finally paid attention that Harry really found it truly arousing. He'd had to ruffle his robes to hide his interest as he watched her eat. Ginny's stuffing was beginning to feel pornographic.

Harry was starting to wonder what might happen if Ginny just kept up her immense appetite until the wedding. In fact, to the thought of Ginny struggling to waddle down the aisle excited him. He was starting to think about just how big Molly Weasley was, and how Ginny already rivalled her weight.

(For those of you who like numbers, Fleur now weighs 136kgs. That is 300lbs. Ginny now weighs 95kg. That's 210lbs.)
